      <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1814-11_page01.jpg"/>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="image1.jpg"/>
            <!--filenames for photos associated with this letter. Example: <pb n="1" facs="image1.jpg image2.jpg image3.jpg"/> -->
            <opener>
               <dateline><!--If there's no date line, omit this element. Record in the order in which it is written on the letter.-->
                  <name type="place" ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworth's Town</name>
                  <lb/>
                  <date when="1814-11-28"/>November 28, 1814. </dateline>
               <salute>
                  My dear Madam,
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p> 
               I have just heard of an excellent <choice><orig>op-<lb/>
               portunity</orig><reg>opportunity</reg></choice> of getting our small parcel<lb/>
               over to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#IE">Ireland</placeName> - a friend of ours is now<lb/>
               at <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Clifton_ENK">Clifton</placeName> &amp; if you will be so good to<lb/>
               send it directed as follows by the coach<lb/>
               it will reach us in due time.<lb/>
            </p>
            <p><persName ref="./Personography.xml#GodlM1">Miss Margaret Godley</persName><lb/>
               <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#14-Hope-Square_ENK">14 Hope Square<lb/>
               Clifton - Bristol</placeName> -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>The parcel should be <unclear>booked</unclear> - &amp; may<lb/>
               be directed on an inside cover to <hi rend="underline">me</hi>.<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>If you have time &amp; opportunity<lb/>
               I should be very much obliged to you<lb/>
               if you would add to my former <choice><orig>com-<lb/>
               missions</orig><reg>commissions</reg></choice> the following<lb/>
            </p>
            <p><unclear></unclear><lb/>
            <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1814-11_page02.jpg"/>

               <note place="bottom">CO962, Edgeworth</note>
               Mechlin lace sent in my last - same as<lb/>
               what you bought for me before for the<lb/>
               bosom of a gown - it is not full enough<lb/>
               for the present mode -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>I should also wish to trouble you to buy<lb/>
               a veil for me - a yard square of fine<lb/>
               clear bobbinet on which you can have<lb/>
               an edge of real lace put at<lb/>
            </p>
            <p><placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Rickwoods_ENK">Rickwoods</placeName> <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#104-Piccadilly_ENK">N<hi rend="superscript">o</hi> 104 Piccadilly</placeName> -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>It is for the sake of your taste in the choice<lb/>
               of the edge that I trouble you with this <choice><orig>com-<lb/>
               mission</orig><reg>commission</reg></choice><lb/>
            </p>
            <p>I saw an edge lately of nearly this pattern<lb/>
               which looked light &amp; elegant<lb/>
               <figure>
                  <figDesc>Pen-drawn illustration of four circles conjoined horizontally which contain a cross-hatched pattern.</figDesc>
               </figure><lb/>
               I do not like deep heavy borders for such<lb/>
               <add>a</add> little creature as I am: but I leave it to your taste.<lb/> 
            
            </p>
            <closer>
               <!--include linebreaks, if used. example: <closer> Yours<lb/> Very sincerely<lb/> -->
            </closer>
